*WARNING* I meant to post this before the pay to get Prime.
Non-Prime is now Unranked. Even if you have Prime, there's a pretty solid chance that you will queue against and/or with Non-Prime players.


As soon as I got rank 2 in order to be able to play Competitive, I started queueing up for Competitive. First game I had a cheater on my team. Second match I had a cheater on both my team and enemy team which I ended up losing because I guess the cheater on my team was the worst out of the two. All of this, is Non-Prime experience. Also, I didn't mention that the most cheaters are in casual and deathmatch games. I also got kicked from a Competitive game when I was their best player(all russian teammates)which they ended up losing that game 16-2. If someone new is supposed to play or at least try to level up to rank 21 to get Prime it would be a hell for them. Valve has stopped caring for Non-Prime, reporting a person through support even with video evidence will get you nowhere. Imagine having an Anti-Cheat that won't detect cheaters and even humans from support deny to see your evidence and are confident about their Anti-Cheat. In my personal opinion, this game is shit if you are Non-Prime. Even in Prime you get cheaters. Valve doesn't care about Counter-Strike anymore. They only care about how they can make money and don't even try to fix their Anti-Cheat. I even messaged them about a forum link where you can code your own free cheats or even get free cheats(THAT IS PUBLIC) and they told me that their Anti-Cheat is handling cheaters. As I said above, it obviously doesn't.


tldr; Don't waste your time in this game's matchmaking. Go for FaceIT or ESEA. These third party people with solid servers and Anti-Cheats are doing a much better work than Shit Valve.
